# Example environment variables for local development / production
# For local development / test without backend, set:
VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA=true

# For production (replace the URL with your backend endpoint):
# VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA=false
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend.example.com/api

# Notes:
# - Vite loads `.env` for dev by default and `.env.production` for build (mode=production).
# - When `VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA=true` the app uses the bundled mock data and doesn't call the backend.
# - When `VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA=false` the app will call `VITE_API_BASE_URL`.
